      "comment": "WHATS THE TEA (8) toughed out a win despite working at this circuit and distance two back before making up plenty of ground but finding one better at his latest appearance at Ballarat. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and the sprint lane is in play so may prove tough to beat. AT THE DISTANCE (3) was held up from the back row at Melton last time but came from wider than this and broke but still managed a very close second at Cranbourne prior. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position and owns a decent record at this circuit and distance. JESSICAS STORY (1) continued her consistent form with a respectable third at her most recent appearance at Maryborough and came from this draw to win three back at Bendigo. BETTOR MAN (4) recorded back-to-back placings then led from this barrier in his last-start fourth at Ballarat. Hasn't missed a place here so respect.",
